Name: Thailand 10-year Government Bond Yield
Periodicity:
Monthly From Dec 1979 To Sep 1999
Daily From Sep 1999 To Mar 2025
Metadata:
Source: Investors Monthly Manual, Bank of Thailand.
Notes: For external bond data, the Siam 4.50% Sterling Bond of 1905 (Redeemable 1945) (BGTHA4505-LO) is used from December 1905 to April 1924 and the Siam 6% Sterling Loan of 1924 (Redeemable 1964) (BGTHA6-LO) is used from May 1924 to January 1936.
The benchmark bond is used for data from December 1979 to date. The benchmark bond is the bond that is closest to the stated maturity without exceeding it. When the government issues a new bond of the stated maturity, it replaces the bond used for the index to keep the maturity as close to the stated time period as possible. Depending on how much of a difference there is in maturities, there may be some adjustment in the yield when the new bond is introduced.
